In [78]:
import pycountry

def country_code_to_name(df):
    return pycountry.countries.get(alpha_2=df['country_code']).name

songs['country_name'] = songs.progress_apply(country_code_to_name, axis=1)

# fix for USA
songs.loc[songs['country_code'] == 'US', 'country_name'] = 'United States of America'
songs.head()

g = songs.groupby('country_name')

g = g.filter(lambda x: len(x) >= 20)
musical_sent = g.groupby(['country_name'])['musical_valence'].mean()
musical_sent = musical_sent.to_frame()
musical_sent.reset_index(inplace=True)
musical_sent.head()

In [83]:



    


country_geo = '../data/world-countries.json'
MAX_RECORDS = 1000

m = folium.Map(location=(START_COORDINATES), zoom_start=2)
folium.Choropleth(geo_data=country_geo, data=musical_sent, 
             key_on='feature.properties.name',columns=['country_name', 'musical_valence'], fill_color='RdYlGn', 
             fill_opacity=0.7, line_opacity=0.2, legend_name='Spotify Valence',
                 nan_fill_color='gray', nan_fill_opacity=0.1).add_to(m)

folium.LayerControl().add_to(m)

m.save(outfile=map_path+'valence_map.html')
m

In [86]:



    


states = ["West Virginia","Alabama","Alaska","Arizona","Arkansas","California","Colorado",
  "Connecticut","Delaware","Florida","Georgia","Hawaii","Idaho","Illinois",
  "Indiana","Iowa","Kansas","Kentucky","Louisiana","Maine","Maryland",
  "Massachusetts","Michigan","Minnesota","Mississippi","Missouri","Montana",
  "Nebraska","Nevada","New Hampshire","New Jersey","New Mexico","New York",
  "North Carolina","North Dakota","Ohio","Oklahoma","Oregon","Pennsylvania",
  "Rhode Island","South Carolina","South Dakota","Tennessee","Texas","Utah",
  "Vermont","Virginia","Washington","Wisconsin","Wyoming"]

def get_state(str):
    i = 0
    while i < len(states):
        if states[i] in str:
            return states[i]
        i += 1

usa['state'] = usa['location'].progress_apply(lambda x: get_state(x))
usa.head()

country_geo = '../data/us-states.json'

m = folium.Map(location=(START_COORDINATES), zoom_start=3)
folium.Choropleth(geo_data=country_geo, data=states_score, 
             key_on='feature.properties.name',columns=['state', 'vader_score'], fill_color='RdYlGn', 
             fill_opacity=0.7, line_opacity=0.2, legend_name='VADER Sentiment Score',
                 nan_fill_color='gray', nan_fill_opacity=0.1).add_to(m)

folium.LayerControl().add_to(m)

m.save(outfile=map_path+'usa_vader_map.html')
m
